{
  "texts": [
    "Due to their diminutive size, these targets embody less information and suffer from reduced resolution, complicating the task of distilling unique features.",
    "Furthermore, they pose annotation challenges and are particularly vulnerable to errors.",
    " The need for precise localization.",
    "Small targets are highly susceptible to environmental changes, making accurate localization critical.",
    "A minor shift, even by one pixel, in prediction can substantially affect the outcome for small targets."
  ]
}